 se-day-2-git-and-github
## Explain the fundamental concepts of version control and why GitHub is a popular tool for managing versions of code. How does version control help in maintaining project integrity?

ANSWERS

version control helps with tracking contributions made by individual team members to a project, git is the most popular version control tool because it enhances collaboration amongst team members, it also allows access to data on github, via searches made by people on search engines.

## Describe the process of setting up a new repository on GitHub. What are the key steps involved, and what are some of the important decisions you need to make during this process?

ANSWERS

use "git init" or the (+) PLUS sign on the top left corner, before this one must have signed up with git or github. next you need to input the name of your repo, then choose if it should be public or private, then choose license if its public, next add a README  and a .Gitignore.

important decisions include: deciding if the code should be public or private also determining the license to use MIT or GPL, Finally adding branch protection rules.

